==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Justifiable
<hw>Jus"ti*fi`a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>justifiable</ets>. See <er>Justify</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of
being justified, or shown to be just.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just are the ways of God,⟦br⟧
And <qex>justifiable</qex> to men.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Defensible; vindicable; warrantable; excusable;
exculpable; authorizable.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Jus"ti*fi`a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Jus"ti*fi`a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Justification</ent>⟦br⟧
